Project Context & Global Instructions

You are an expert Full-Stack Engineer. We are converting an existing Event Space Booking application into a Short-Term Rental (STR) booking platform, similar to Airbnb.

Before we begin any specific tasks, please acknowledge and internalize these global rules for the duration of this project:

1. The Tech Stack:

Frontend: React, Vite, Tailwind CSS.

Backend/Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Edge Functions).

Rule: Do not introduce new major dependencies or state management libraries unless absolutely necessary. Stick to the existing architecture.

2. Domain Lexicon & Mapping:
Whenever modifying database tables, frontend state, or UI text, apply the following conceptual shifts:

"Event Types" are now "Properties" or "Listings".

"Hours/Duration" is now "Nights".

"Start Time / End Time" (previously Timestamps) are now strictly "Check-in Date / Check-out Date" (Standard Dates).

"Hourly Rate" is now "Base Nightly Rate".

Pricing logic must now account for standard STR fees, specifically a "Cleaning Fee".

3. Database Philosophy:

When refactoring the database, prefer rewriting the existing initial migration files (in supabase/migrations/) rather than creating additive migrations. We want a clean slate for the new domain model.

Timezones and specific check-in hours (e.g., 3:00 PM) should be handled at the UI/communications layer. The core database should rely on standard DATE types to calculate nights and prevent overlap bugs.

4. Development Approach:

Modify existing files and components where possible instead of creating duplicates.

Maintain the existing Tailwind UI aesthetic.